.TH ABRAFLEXI-UPREPORT 1 "2025-09-20" "abraflexi-report-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-upreport \- upload AbraFlexi custom report files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-upreport
.I recordIdent
.I "report name"
.I formInfoCode
.I reportfile
[\fIattachment\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-upreport
uploads a custom report definition to AbraFlexi.
If the main report file is a
.I .jrxml
file, it is compiled using
.BR jaspercompiler (1)
before upload.
Additional files such as translations, images, or other resources can be attached
to the report in the same invocation.
.PP
If the target report record does not yet exist, the tool creates it using the
supplied record identifier, report name, and form information code.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I recordIdent
AbraFlexi record identifier, for example
.BR code:PokladDen .
.TP
.I "report name"
Human-readable report name shown in AbraFlexi.
.TP
.I formInfoCode
AbraFlexi form information code for the target agenda.
.TP
.I reportfile
Main report file to upload. This is usually a
.I .jrxml
or
.I .jasper
file.
.TP
.I attachment
Optional additional files bundled with the report, such as
.I localization.json
or image assets.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The tool reads AbraFlexi connection settings via
\fBEase\\Shared::init()\fR
from environment variables or a local
.I .env
file:
.BR ABRAFLEXI_URL ,
.BR ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN ,
.BR ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD ,
and
.BR ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Upload a report source file and attachments:
.B abraflexi-upreport code:PokladDen "My Report" pokDenik report.jrxml localization.json logo.png
.TP
Upload a precompiled Jasper file:
.B abraflexi-upreport code:TEST "My Report" formInfoCode report.jasper
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-previewreport (1),
.BR abraflexi-repxmlunpacker (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Vítězslav Dvořák